  <title>Histogram</title>

  <warning><para>This section of the manual is out of date! It has not been updated yet to reflect the changes made in the current
   development version of OVITO.</para></warning>

  <para>
  
    <informalfigure><screenshot><mediaobject><imageobject>
       <imagedata fileref="images/modifiers/histogram_panel.png" format="PNG" />
    </imageobject></mediaobject></screenshot></informalfigure>
  
    This modifier computes a histogram of the values of a particle or bond property. 
  </para>
  
  <para>
    Additionally, the modifier allows to select all particles or bonds whose property values
    lie within a certain interval.
  </para>
  
  <simplesect>
    <title>Parameters</title>

    <variablelist>

      <varlistentry>
        <term>Input</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>Selects whether input property values should be taken from particles or bonds.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    
      <varlistentry>
        <term>Property</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>The particle or bond property the histogram should be computed for.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term>Number of histogram bins</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>Controls the resolution of the generated histogram.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term>Use only selected particles/bonds</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>Restricts the histogram calculation to the subset of particles or bonds that are currently selected.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term>Select value range</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>Lets the modifier select all particles or bonds whose property value lies in the specified range.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      
    </variablelist>
  </simplesect>
    
  <simplesect>
  <title>See also</title>
    <para>
      <link xlink:href="python/modules/ovito_modifiers.html#ovito.modifiers.HistogramModifier"><classname>HistogramModifier</classname> (Python API)</link>
    </para>
  </simplesect>  
    
</section>
